    <h1>Over 90,000 peo&#xAD;ple flee wild&#xAD;fires near LA</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201028/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-28"><time>2020-10-28</time></a>
        - <span>WORLD</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>IRVINE • More than 90,000 peo­ple fled their homes near Los An­ge­les on Mon­day as two wild­fires raged across more than 5,900ha, block­ing key road­ways and crit­i­cally in­jur­ing two fire­fight­ers.</p>
    <p>The larger Sil­ver­ado Fire erupted early in the morn­ing in the foothills of Irvine and quickly spread, fu­elled by dry con­di­tions and er­ratic winds.</p>
    <p>A sec­ond blaze about 27km away in Yorba Linda, dubbed the Blue Ridge Fire, erupted in the af­ter­noon.</p>


